<section id="welcome-intro">
  <div class="container opening__layout">
    <div>
      <pre><code class="highlight"><span class="k">require</span> <span class="s">'headius/welcome'</span></code></pre>
      <hgroup>
        <h1>Welcome to Headius!</h1>
        <p>Headius Enterprises provides support and services to users of JRuby and related technologies. Through this work, we have become the primary funding source for the JRuby project and its development.</p>
        <p>Your partnership with Headius Enterprises ensures the future of JRuby and supports the ongoing development of the open source JRuby ecosystem.</p>
      </hgroup>
      <div class="welcome-cta">
        <a class="button" href="<%= relative_url '/services' %>">Support.packages</a>
        <a class="button ghost" href="<%= relative_url '/about' %>">Headius.about</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <img src="/images/he-logo.svg" alt="Headius Enterprises" class="opening__logo" />
  </div>
</section>

<section class="highlight">
  <div class="container">
    <pre><code class="highlight"><span class="c"># == Headius::Origin</span>
<span class="c"># The name goes back to 1992.</span></code></pre>
    <h2>Why "Headius"?</h2>
    <p>
      The Headius name has been associated with Chief Architect Charles Oliver Nutter since 1992, carrying with it three decades of open source management and contribution. Our commitment to the Free and Open Source Software community is at the core of everything we do.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="container">
    <pre><code class="highlight"><span class="c"># == Headius::Partnership</span>
<span class="c"># A win-win model.</span></code></pre>
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>
      JRuby development is funded through support subscriptions and contracts with Headius Enterprises. It's a win-win partnership: your applications receive ongoing support from the people who actually build JRuby, while JRuby continues to thrive as an open source project.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you are a user of JRuby, you can partner with Headius Enterprises by signing up for one of our JRuby Support tiers. You can choose from our already packaged support levels, or we will work with you to right-size a support contract that guarantees your team will have access to expert JRuby maintainers on demand. JRuby support will protect your critical applications from unforseen problems and connect your development team directly to JRuby experts around the globe.
    </p>
    <p>
      Choose the level of support that fits your team — or <a href="<%= relative_url '/contact' %>">get in touch</a> if you need something custom.
    </p>
    <div class="welcome-cta">
      <a class="button" href="<%= relative_url '/services' %>">Support.packages</a>
      <a class="button ghost" href="<%= relative_url '/about' %>">Headius.about</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
